==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rewel bone
<hw>Rew"el bone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Perh. from F.
<ets>rouelle</ets>, dim. of <ets>roue</ets> a wheel, L.
<ets>rota</ets>.]</ety> <def>An obsolete phrase of disputed meaning, --
perhaps, smooth or polished bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His saddle was of <qex>rewel boon</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rewet</ent>⟦br⟧
